What is HTML?

HTML stands for Hyper Text Markup language. This language help us to build semantics of the website. For example: Adding Button, Radio and checkboxes, Table, Dropdown, Layouts etc.

HTML Tags Types:

1. Container tags
2. Self closing tags

Basic HTML tags:

1. Div
2. Section
3. Main
4. Html
5. Head
6. Body
7. Span
8. Header
9. Footer
10. Anchor - a

Container Tags:
A container tags will helps us to wrap and contain multiple other elements inside it.

Example:

1. Html
2. Head
3. Body
4. Div
5. Section
6. Span
7. Header
8. Footer

Self closing tags or HTML Elements:
HTML Elements are tags that help us to get user input in the form of text or color or boolean or MCQ or Range.

Examples:

1. Input - Text, Password, Date, Time, Checkbox, Radio, Range, Color
2. Select - Dropdown
3. Textarea - Textbox

Basic Page Syntax:

<html>
<head>
 // For configuration
</head>
<body>
// Adding all elements
// Layouts
</body>
</html>

Based on Semantics, tags are of two different types:

1. Semantic - If we can understand the base meaning of that tag name its semantic
2. Non-Semantic - Else non-semantic
